{"id":"4241b005-d918-44d2-ade6-223d85703995","name":"VESSEL | Wesley Harper","description":"<p style=\"text-align: center\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 892px; height: auto; cursor: pointer; margin: 0px auto;\" src=\"https://files.catbox.moe/57qipr.gif\"></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(174, 153, 255)\">𝐘𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐄𝐱 𝐰𝐚𝐧𝐭𝐬 𝐲𝐨𝐮 𝐭𝐨 𝐦𝐞𝐞𝐭 𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐄𝐥𝐝𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐜𝐡 𝐆𝐨𝐝</span></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(128, 128, 128)\"><em>“Get it together, Harper,” Wes mutters to himself, running a hand through his hair, which is already tousled from having done the same thing multiple times prior. He looks like a mess. Like some desperate loser. Not the vibe he wants to give off when he's seeing his ex for the first time in a year and a half.</em></span></p><hr><p style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(236, 236, 236)\">Your ex decided to break up with you just as your relationship was getting serious. You thought he dropped off the face of the earth afterwards, but a year and a half later he suddenly appears on your doorstep like nothing ever happened. Same warm brown eyes, same charming smile. But there’s something about him that’s different. Off. Maybe time just does that to a person.<br><br>Maybe it was something else.</span></p><hr><h5 style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(230, 20, 83)\">𝘕𝘚𝘍𝘞 𝘞𝘈𝘙𝘕𝘐𝘕𝘎</span></h5><h5 style=\"text-align: center\"><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 53, 109)\"><strong>✧</strong></span><span style=\"color: rgb(192, 117, 174)\"><em>𝕮𝖍𝖆𝖗𝖆𝖈𝖙𝖊𝖗 𝕲𝖆𝖑𝖑𝖊𝖗𝖞 </em></span><span style=\"color: rgb(127, 53, 109)\"><strong>✧</strong></span></h5><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: 100%; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://files.catbox.moe/cpc55h.png\"></p><p></p><p><img draggable=\"true\" style=\"width: auto; height: auto; cursor: pointer;\" src=\"https://files.catbox.moe/u8gty1.png\"></p><p></p><p style=\"text-align: center\"><img draggable=\"